in function `public static void setVisible(final int index, final boolean visible)`

https://github.com/cocos2d/cocos2d-x/blob/v3/cocos/platform/android/java/src/org/cocos2dx/lib/Cocos2dxEditBoxHelper.java#L311-L317

``` java
                    if (visible) {
                        editBox.requestFocus();
                        Cocos2dxEditBoxHelper.openKeyboard(index);
                    }else{
                        mCocos2dxActivity.getGLSurfaceView().requestFocus();
                        Cocos2dxEditBoxHelper.closeKeyboard(index);
                    }
```

Set visibility of EditBox will also toggles keyboard. We should not do this, see the follow scenario:
- I have a EditSettingsDialog with 2 EditBox: `a` (single line edit) and `b` (multiple line edit).
- When i open EditSettingsDialog I my specify which EditBox to be visible.

``` Lua
function EditSettingsDialog:openSingleLine()
    a:setVisible(true) 
    b:setVisible(false)
end

function EditSettingsDialog:openMultipleLine()
    a:setVisible(false)
    b:setVisible(true)
end
```
- `EditSettingsDialog:openSingleLine()` will opens keyboard and then close keyboard, final status will **have no keyboard**.
- `EditSettingsDialog:openMultipleLine()` will close keyboard and then open keyboard, final status will **have keyboard**.

